---
import Article from "../../../layouts/Article.astro";
import KeyTakeaway from "../../../components/KeyTakeaway.astro";
import InfoBox from "../../../components/InfoBox.astro";
---

<Article
  title="How Does Terraforming Rating (TR) Work in Terraforming Mars?"
  description="TR is your income AND your score. Here's how it works and why it's the most important number in the game."
  game="terraforming-mars"
  gameTitle="Terraforming Mars"
  category="Rules"
  publishDate="2025-05-06"
>
  <p>
    Terraforming Rating is the single most important number in Terraforming Mars.
    It's your income, it's part of your final score, and it's how you win. Yet
    many new players underestimate it.
  </p>

  <KeyTakeaway answer="Your Terraforming Rating (TR) starts at 20. It goes up when you raise a global parameter (temperature, oxygen, or oceans). TR serves double duty: it's your M€ income each generation AND it counts as victory points at game end." />

  <h2>How TR Works</h2>

  <div class="my-6 space-y-4">
    <div class="p-5 bg-white rounded-xl border-l-4 border-clay">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
        <span class="px-2.5 py-0.5 bg-clay/10 text-clay text-xs font-bold rounded-full">Income</span>
        <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-bark">TR = M€ Per Generation</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">
        During the production phase, you receive M€ equal to your TR plus your M€ production.
        A TR of 25 with M€ production of 10 means you get 35 M€ each generation.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="p-5 bg-white rounded-xl border-l-4 border-clay">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
        <span class="px-2.5 py-0.5 bg-clay/10 text-clay text-xs font-bold rounded-full">Scoring</span>
        <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-bark">TR = Victory Points</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">
        At game end, your TR counts directly as VP. If you end the game at TR 35,
        that's 35 victory points just from TR — before adding greenery tiles, city tiles,
        awards, milestones, and card VP.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="p-5 bg-white rounded-xl border-l-4 border-clay">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
        <span class="px-2.5 py-0.5 bg-clay/10 text-clay text-xs font-bold rounded-full">How to Raise</span>
        <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-bark">Terraform to Earn TR</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">
        Every time you raise temperature (1 step), oxygen (1%), or place an ocean tile,
        your TR goes up by 1. Some cards also directly increase TR.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>TR Earning Actions</h2>

  <div class="my-6 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-bark/10">
    <table class="w-full text-sm">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th class="text-left p-3 bg-bark/[0.02] font-heading font-semibold text-bark/70">Action</th>
          <th class="text-center p-3 bg-bark/[0.02] font-heading font-semibold text-bark/70">TR Gained</th>
          <th class="text-left p-3 bg-bark/[0.02] font-heading font-semibold text-bark/70">Cost</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr class="border-t border-bark/5"><td class="p-3">Raise temperature 1 step</td><td class="p-3 text-center">+1</td><td class="p-3 text-bark/50">8 heat</td></tr>
        <tr class="border-t border-bark/5"><td class="p-3">Raise oxygen 1%</td><td class="p-3 text-center">+1</td><td class="p-3 text-bark/50">Place a greenery tile (8 plants)</td></tr>
        <tr class="border-t border-bark/5"><td class="p-3">Place ocean tile</td><td class="p-3 text-center">+1</td><td class="p-3 text-bark/50">Various (standard project: 18 M€)</td></tr>
        <tr class="border-t border-bark/5 bg-amber-50/50"><td class="p-3 font-semibold">Some project cards</td><td class="p-3 text-center font-bold">+1 to +3</td><td class="p-3 text-bark/50">Varies by card</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2>Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="my-6 space-y-3">
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-blue-50 rounded-xl border border-blue-100">
      <span class="text-lg shrink-0">❓</span>
      <div>
        <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm text-blue-800">"Can TR go down?"</h4>
        <p class="text-sm text-blue-700/70 mt-1"><strong>Rarely.</strong> A few cards and the Turmoil expansion can lower TR. In the base game, TR almost always only goes up.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-blue-50 rounded-xl border border-blue-100">
      <span class="text-lg shrink-0">❓</span>
      <div>
        <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm text-blue-800">"Should I prioritize TR over card VP?"</h4>
        <p class="text-sm text-blue-700/70 mt-1"><strong>Usually yes, early on.</strong> TR gains compound — each TR point earns you M€ every remaining generation. Early TR is like compound interest. Late-game, card VP might be more efficient.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <InfoBox type="tip" title="The TR Mindset">
    Think of every TR point as a permanent raise. If you gain 1 TR in generation 3 and the game lasts 10 generations, that 1 TR earned you 7 extra M€ over the game PLUS 1 VP at the end. Early terraforming is almost always correct.
  </InfoBox>
</Article>
